
Taylor’s Uni Smart Clinic is a prototype system that contributes to the Sustainable Development Goal 3 Good Health and Wellbeing. 
The system enables students to access health care services with less waiting time at their university by allowing students to manage 
their appointments online. They can create their accounts to view the list of doctors, book appointments, as well as cancel or change them 
according to their needs. Doctors will be able to access their daily appointments and add notes to for their consultation. Admin will be able to 
manage student and doctor accounts, as well as see activity at the clinic.
This system will make it easier for students to access university clinic appointments and save time
